Package: symengine
Title: Interface to the SymEngine Library
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Jialin", "Ma", email="marlin@inventati.org", role = c("cre", "aut")),
             person("Isuru", "Fernando", email="isuruf@gmail.com", role = c("aut")),
             person("Xin", "Chen", email="xinchen.tju@gmail.com", role = c("aut")))
Description: SymEngine <https://github.com/symengine/> is a standalone C++ library for
    fast symbolic manipulation. It aims to serve as a fast core of SymPy computer algebra
    system in Python and allow usages from other programming languages such as Julia.
    This package provides an R interface to SymEngine, which can be used for calculating
    exact mathematical expressions, solving systems of linear equations, generating
    C/MathML/LaTeX/JavaScript code string from symbolic expressions, etc.
